	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1331234">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1331234">
                  
                  Here is a very simple reason why the developers will look peculiar, to say the least, if this revamp takes place in June/July/August without almost any changes:  <br />
<br />
If there are minimal changes to what already is known will be implemented why was it delayed?  A revamp is supposed to enhance and improve a class therefore it should have gone in as quickly as possible.  Either it is viewed as less than a revamp and unimportant so that it is meaningless to postpone or it is actually a reduction in dps and thus its effects HAVE to be masked by putting it alongside the melee changes.  Whichever reason it would be both are absurd.  The class that will be perhaps most in need of a revamp after the 5th update having one of the worst revamps?  <br />
<br />
If the revamp was delayed because it is actually harmful to sorcerer dps or was not considered very important is it actually a &quot;revamp&quot; at all?   <br />
<br />
For these reaasons the developers simply can't logically commit themselves to sealing off all possible changes to the revamp list.  Why delay it if not to get some extra time to make it better?  First a class lead will be needed to assist with extensive dps testing and there should be an major examination of the class's utility.  There is some much good material to choose from on these forums and the feedback that it would be almost beyond belief if none of these suggestions were taken into account.  <br />
<br />
<br />
The Seradon's Falling Star changes do significantly increase dps.  Flamespear has a large bonus on critical hits.  However spells such as Taqmir's Barrage and Char should be looked at.  Char should have its dot damage increased and the effect increased to 6 seconds which would match the refresh time and differentiate it further.  The base damage on Taqmir's Barrage may need change also.  Chaos Volley is more of a group spell now that is boosts spell damage.  <br />
<br />
The forms are somewhat helpful in terms of dps and flavor.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2">
		<img class="inlineimg" src="images/legacy_images/statusicon/user_offline.gif" alt="SphereofLight is offline" border="0" />


		
		
		
