		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1331877">
                  
                  <div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Sasami</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Oh, I know a previous funcom product and I wish you all the luck with AoC, you will need it. <br />
<br />
If I remember right, the bugs reported in regards to the old stances were not minor. I&#8217;m to lazy to search for the posts but maybe Illusive still remembers what he posted from the testing at that time.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
asaya's guile: <br />
unable to mez any mob while in the form NONE.  if you mezed a mob out of the form and then switched to it, and re-casted mez it would break immidiately.<br />
<br />
- 5% hate pool reduction per cast, was actually doing +5% hate pool per cast.  This would make a sorc pull agro after casting 5-6 taq's barrage even if you waited till 80% to nuke (on raid targets)<br />
<br />
and in small groups you would always be the tank unless you stood there doing nothing.<br />
<br />
<br />
seradon's intensity:<br />
power cost was too large, the +75% energy cost equated to double the rate of energy consumption.  for solo you couldn't kill a 4 dot mob because you'd run out of energy (this is with a full heroic high elf toon with max wisdom / int)<br />
<br />
it took too long to ramp up to the max level (5th level) to get +60% damage.  (IE 20-25 seconds)<br />
<br />
by then you were almost out of energy.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
also a bug with the forms that when you killed a mob, you incurred lockout and couldn't switch forms for the duration of the lockout,    IE nuke 2 dot mob to dead in burn form, then you had to wait 8 seconds to switch to asaya's guile or unfocused to regain your endurance to use gather energy.<br />
<br />
<br />
problem with regaining lost energy while in seradons intensity: gather energy didn't work because it reduced your endurance to zero, and energy shard is 1 hour recast and 10minute re-use.<br />
<br />
<br />
general bug with the forms not staying &quot;charged&quot; up after each mob kill. Instead it would re-set to zero after the mob died, and if you untargeted the mob it would decay at a rapid rate.<br />
<br />
IE start nuking a mob get &quot;seradons intensity to max rank&quot; then switch to an add to mez it, and swap back seradons intensity would be at rank 3.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
what they were supposed to do/fix:<br />
<br />
fix detaunt on asaya's guile,<br />
fix mez bug on asaya's guile,<br />
fix form switching bug when mob died,<br />
<br />
reduce energy shard to 15m recast<br />
modify how gather energy works to not take endurance<br />
<br />
make seradons intensity provide max bonus +75% energy cost and give +60% damage increase off the bat.  (IE no scaling up or down always on while in the form)<br />
make asaya's guile give max bonus -30% energy cost and -5% hate detaunt right off the bat.<br />
<br />
now take that, and add in the seradons falling star changes<br />
<br />
reverse most of the flame spear changes<br />
<br />
add in the fire / ice synergy everyone wanted<br />
<br />
add in the antimagic aura's / sanctuary's<br />
<br />
add in asaya's scorn<br />
<br />
<br />
and boom you have a revamp that sorcerer's could be proud of.<br />
<br />
<br />
max dps in burn form would of come from using flamespear + seradons falling star, you would go empty pretty quick but you would out dps CV for a short time frame.<br />
<br />
CV + asaya's guile was to be our efficient stance for long power consuming fights.
                  
		</div>
